Change the @{"default public screen" link "Glossary" 0} to the currently selected public screen.

Hotkey: @{fg highlight}Amiga-D@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "Front_GUI" "To Front: Bring a public screen to the front (GUI)"
@{fg highlight}Screen ģ To Front@{fg text}

Bring the selected public screen to the front of the display. A shortcut is to
double-click on the screen's name in the list.

Hotkey: @{fg highlight}Amiga-F@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "Back_GUI" "To Back: Push a public screen to the back (GUI)"
@{fg highlight}Screen ģ To Back@{fg text}

Push the selected public screen to the back of the display. This is probably
of limited usefulness.

Hotkey: @{fg highlight}Amiga-B@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "Info_GUI" "Information: Get information on a public screen (GUI)"
@{fg highlight}Screen ģ Information...@{fg text}

Get information on the currently selected public screen. Information includes
the screen's title, public screen name, display identifier, resolution, depth,
and font.

Under Release 3, the information requester also indicates if the screen's
bitmap is @{"interleaved" link "Glossary" 32}.

Hotkey: @{fg highlight}Amiga-I@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "Palette_GUI" "Palette: Change a public screen's palette (GUI)"
@{fg highlight}Screen ģ Palette...@{fg text}

Change the palette of the currently selected public screen, using the reqtools
palette requester.

Hotkey: @{fg highlight}Amiga-P@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "WritePalette_GUI" "Write Palette: Save a screen's palette (GUI)"
@{fg highlight}Screen ģ Write Palette...@{fg text}

Save the palette of the selected screen as a macro. This macro can be used to
set the colors of the screen by executing it later.

Hotkey: @{fg highlight}Amiga-W@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "Jump_GUI" "Jump Window: Jump the window to another public screen (GUI)"
@{fg highlight}Tools ģ Jump Window@{fg text}

Makes the control window appear on the currently selected public screen. This
screen will pop to the front, and the window will be made active.

Hotkey: @{fg highlight}Amiga-J@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "Update_GUI" "Update Display: Update the control window (GUI)"
@next "Macro_GUI"
@{fg highlight}Tools ģ Update Display@{fg text}

Update the control window display. This is sometimes necessary after closing a
public screen.

Under ScreenFool 2.4U and later, this forces the reloading of the display mode
list. This is useful after opening another monitor or changing locales.

In future, an automated update may be done for locale changes.

Hotkey: @{fg highlight}Amiga-U@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "UserHelp_GUI" "Help: Get information on ScreenFool commands"
@{fg highlight}Tools ģ Help...@{fg text}

This option allows the user to get direct help on the gadgets on the screen.
In the requester, enter the name of the gadget you want information on.

Hotkey: @{fg highlight}Amiga-L@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "MacroMenu_GUI" "Macro ģ Script Menu (GUI)"
@{fg highlight}Macro ģ Script Menu@{fg text}

Use @{"Macro ģ Script ģ Console..." link "MacCon_GUI" 0} for an output window, or use
@{"Macro ģ Script ģ No Console..." link "Macro_GUI" 0} for a script without a window.
@endnode

